%N A280207 Decimal expansion of x such that tan(Pi/x) + sin(Pi/x)*cos(Pi/x) = 2*Pi/x.
%C A280207 This is the hypothetical number of sides an equilateral polygon would have to have in order to create the same area between it and a circle in both its inscribed and circumscribed forms.
%C A280207 It is probably transcendental, though that has not been proved.
%C A280207 The constant is transcendental: if x is rational than the LHS is algebraic and the RHS is transcendental; else Gelfond-Schneider forces an algebraic relationship between Pi and exp(I*Pi/x). - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 23 2026
%H A280207 Ondrej Hrdina, <a href="http://pastebin.com/raw/ELZh63gv">First 50000 digits</a>.
%H A280207 Ondrej Hrdina, <a href="https://redd.it/5ky9tx">In-depth description</a>. [Broken link]
